Package ispd.motor.workload.impl

Class TraceFileWorkloadGenerator

java.lang.Object
ispd.motor.workload.impl.TraceFileWorkloadGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
WorkloadGenerator
public class TraceFileWorkloadGenerator extends Object implements WorkloadGenerator
Generates a workload from parsing a trace file, and evenly distributes the tasks of such workload among all masters in a GridQueueNetwork.
Some particularities:
  • How the class interprets information gathered from the trace file about a task depends on its traceType. See TraceTaskBuilder and ExternalTraceTaskBuilder for their differences.
  • It updates the GridQueueNetwork with information about the users found in the tasks read from the trace file.

  • Constructor Details

    • TraceFileWorkloadGenerator

      public TraceFileWorkloadGenerator (File traceFile, int taskCount, String traceType)
      Instantiate a generator with the given properties of a trace file.
      Parameters:
      traceFile - the trace File that will be processed. The file should exist.
      taskCount - the number of tasks to be processed from the trace file. Must be positive and non-strictly less than the number of actual tasks present in the trace file.
      traceType - the type of trace being processed; it will affect the interpretation of certain task properties read from the file. It must be one of {iSPD, SWF, GWF}

      public List<GridTask> makeTaskList (GridQueueNetwork qn)
      Creates a task list from the trace file, updates the given GridQueueNetwork and its schedulers with information about the users found in the trace, and distributes the generated tasks evenly among all masters.
      Specified by:
      makeTaskList in interface WorkloadGenerator
      Parameters:
      qn - GridQueueNetwork with masters that will host the GridTasks.
      Returns:
      List of GridTasks generated.
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the number of tasks to be generated (i.e., taskCount) exceeds the number of tasks in the trace file; which may happen if there was an error collecting the tasks from the file.
